metadata.name: Fisherman
metadata.description:
Maybe the fisherman wanted to wake up in the land of ice, to the bright dreams of a morning as sharp as a polished sword...Who knows it might be his own dreams, not the frozen lake... Desperation in the face of the cold was turning into a giant monument instead of an ice sculpture with the blazing fire of labor; his labor monument!

**I am a Turkish documentary photographer. I produce photographs about people and life.**

**Camera:** Nikon D810
**Lens:** Nikkor 14-24 mm
**Dimensions:** 4897 ×3265
**Resolution:** 300 dpi
**Location:** Konya,Turkey
**Date:** 01/01/2022
**Edition:** 1/1
